What is $\dbinom{n}{n}$ for any positive integer $n$?
inference:
By definition, $\dbinom{n}{n} = \frac{n!}{n! \cdot 0!}$

As $0! = 1$, the formula becomes $\dbinom{n}{n} = \frac{n!}{n!} = 1.$
 
Final Answer: $\boxed{1}.$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: $\dbinom{n}{n}=\dfrac{n!}{n!0!}=\boxed{1}$.  Also, there is only one way to choose $n$ objects out of $n$, which is simply choosing all of them.
